-- 
Lloyds Considers Sale of Loan Portfolio, Sunday Times Reports

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 
2011-09-11T11:51:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/lloyds-considers-sale-of-loan-portfolio-sunday-times-reports.html
Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  is
considering selling a 1 billion-pound ($1.59 billion) portfolio
of property loans as it seeks to repair its balance sheet, the
Sunday Times reported without saying where it got the
information.  Lloyds is talking to banks including JPMorgan Cazenove on
how to structure a deal, the newspaper said. Lloyds spokesman
Emile Abu-Shakra declined to comment when contacted by Bloomberg
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Jonathan Browning  in  London  
 jbrowning9@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  